{"type":"message","id":"230f69d2","parentId":"dee31bed","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:58:39.334Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is from Moltbook - specifically a JSON parse error when trying to fetch posts. This could be:\n1. The Moltbook API returning an error page instead of JSON\n2. A network issue with cloudflared tunnel (since Moltbook uses that)\n3. The API key might be expired or invalid\n\nThe last moltbook check was at 1742749080 (which is around ~2 hours ago based on current time of 1742835473 - wait, let me recalculate).\n\nCurrent time: 2026-03-24T13:57:00Z = 1742829420\nLast moltbook check: 1742749080\nDifference: 1742829420 - 1742749080 = 80,340 seconds = 22.3 hours\n\nWait, that doesn't match \"moltbook_interval_minutes\": 60. Let me recalculate...\n\nActually, 1742835473 (current) - 1742749080 = 86,393 seconds = 24 hours ago.\n\nHmm, but that's not the immediate issue. The immediate issue is that JSON parse error from the Moltbook API. The error message says:\n`\"Expected property name or '}' in JSON at position 1 (line 1 column 2)\"`\n\nThis means the response started with something like `{` which is valid, but position 1 after that would be an issue. Wait, actually the error says \"at position 1 (line 1 column 2)\" - this typically means the response body isn't JSON.\n\nActually, the session \"mellow-r\" had an exec that returned code 1 with a 400 error. This was a failed exec command. The error is from an HTTP request to `/api/v1/posts/aa9e7484-1790-4d51…` - looks like it was trying to get a specific post.\n\nThis is a background exec that failed. \n\nSince this is a 400 error from Moltbook rather than a cron configuration issue, it's likely either a malformed post ID or an API problem on their end. I should alert Zach about this since it's preventing the background check from completing successfully.","thinkingSignature":"7e92440abb691fcb44790b2532e6b0fd600d7cd694598e050849b2d1851df48d"},{"type":"text","text":"<final>\n**Moltbook API error detected** — a background exec failed with a 400 JSON parse error when fetching a post (`/api/v1/posts/aa9e7484-...`). This looks like the Moltbook API returned a non-JSON response (possibly an error page or redirect) rather than the expected post data.\n\n**Likely causes:**\n1. The cloudflared tunnel to Moltbook may be stale or returning an error page\n2. The post ID may be malformed or the post was deleted\n3. The API key might need refreshing (it was refreshed 2026-03-21)\n\n**Quick check:** If you're able to access Moltbook normally on your end, this might be a transient API glitch. If the tunnel URL changed, the webhook/cron jobs might be pointing to the wrong endpoint.\n\nDo you want me to investigate the cron setup for Moltbook, or is this just a one-off blip you've seen before?\n</final>"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1000,"output":658,"cacheRead":11058,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":12716,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774360701194}}
